column5: Splashhopper and Dutchy were there... saw slowpoke and skinny there... along with Ryan ( at "work" )
Wanted to be, but got talked into moving furniture to-nite instead (yuk).    How was the show/turn out ?
The place was full.... some good info shared that I will keep in mind while jig fishing and bottom bouncing.
Had a blast great to finally meet Ryan and wish slowpoke a happy birthday. Didn't have time to say hi to our hosts  this time around
Good show and lots of laughs, especially the 104 year old security guard faux pas! It was good to see everyone again!
Good to meet some people again, Slowpoke we need to get after some musky this summer
I was there talked to Ryan before going in and my little guy had a accident so I had to leave right away great show Dave's a funny guy
I was there and it was an awesome crowd tonight!! (I was the guy walking around with the camera around my neck)...looking foward to Barrie tomorrow!

That was you 104 year old Bday reach around no mistake there. What a better way to spend the Bday other then being out there fishing.  I might just get out Thursday depending on the time I get done work as I just found out its good Friday and we are off work WOO HOO
No kiddin! We were beside eachother a few times; in the lobby and at the back row of the theater.
hey it was a great show was good to see few people again. I was lucky enough to catch some line. oh and splash shoot me a pm or e-mail about the reel we spoke about.
I was there it was a good show.
Uhhg... I was going to the one tonite but I aint driving 3 hours in this storm... bummer.
I was there with my son. He was telling my wife the minnow bucket story this morning.
Brandon you were right infront of me taking pics I was the guy in the front row with the little guy in a camo hat thought you looked familiar.
you know we should get some other good way of telling who is who out there at shows and such I sat right beside splashopper and didn't even realize it and we met once before.
Yep, if he hadn't mentioned Delhi, and I didn't mention Deer Creek, we would not have known... and I sold skinny my pontoon boat last year
